# CSS Conventions

## Always use CSS custom properties for colours and sizing

All tokens are defined in `:root`. Never hard-code hex values or pixel sizes outside of `:root`.

Key tokens:
- `--bg`, `--surface`, `--text`, `--muted`, `--border`
- `--accent`, `--accent-hover`, `--danger`, `--danger-hover`
- `--control-height: 44px` — shared height for all inputs and buttons
- `--radius: 10px` — card/modal border radius
- `--shadow` — standard box shadow

## Dark mode
The app supports a user-controlled light/dark toggle stored in `localStorage` (`key: 'theme'`, values `'dark'` or `'light'`). `js/theme.js` sets a `data-theme` attribute on `<html>`.

CSS rule:
- `:root` — light defaults (always)
- `@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) { :root:not([data-theme="light"]) { … } }` — auto dark (no user override)
- `[data-theme="dark"] { … }` — explicit dark override (same token values as above)
- `[data-theme="light"] { color-scheme: light; }` — force light browser chrome

Never use class-based dark mode. Never hard-code theme colours outside `:root` / the `[data-theme]` blocks.

## Controls panel — 3-column grid system

All three rows of `.controls-panel` share `grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr)`:
- `.controls-inputs` — file picker | custom header | batch tags
- `.controls-actions` — Upload Content | Export JSON | Clear all data
- `.controls-filter` — flex row (single line): Import JSON + radios | search | clear

Use `gap: 1px; background: var(--border)` on the grid to render hairline dividers between cells without double borders. Child cells get `background: var(--surface)`.

## Group cards — CSS multi-column layout

```css
.groups {
  column-count: 3;
  column-gap: 0.75rem;
}
.group {
  break-inside: avoid;   /* prevent a card from splitting across columns */
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}
```
Expanding a card only shifts items below it in the **same column** — siblings in other columns are unaffected.
Responsive: `column-count: 2` ≤ 860 px, `column-count: 1` ≤ 540 px.
Order is column-major (fills col 1 top→bottom, then col 2, col 3).

## Control sizing

All interactive controls (`input`, `button`, `.chip-input`) must set:
```css
min-height: var(--control-height);
box-sizing: border-box;
```

## `.group` uses container queries
`.group` has `container-type: inline-size` so child rules can respond to card width.

## Empty state spans all columns
```css
.empty-state { column-span: all; }
```
